ods.\n- Repository search shows those `StandardReflectionDriver` setter methods are declarations only; normal ClassGraph public APIs use field reads/method invocation paths, not these setters.\n- The remaining `tryMakeAccessible` site is the pre-JDK-9 fallback after `trySetAccessible`. On the current JDK, `trySetAccessible()` exists and returns normally, so the fallback path is not reachable through normal supported behavior.\n\nCovering these would require direct reflection into package-private internals, placing tests in the library package, mutating private static driver state, or forcing obsolete JDK/security-manager behavior, which would violate the test rules.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_06477cfbd20c6a14016a244c82d710819380b740f2eb4e0f91\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1146, "output": 578, "cacheRead": 57344, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 59068, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1780763768972, "responseId": "resp_06477cfbd20c6a14016a244c79f00081939fd7fba71559c66f"}, "toolResults": []}
